RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOCIAL SUCCESS was rated early and moved to the outside four wide, made a three wide bid on the turn, took over leaving the turn and drew clear to prove best under a drive. PRECIOUS AVARY was bumped at the start, then was well placed towards the inside, was boxed nearing the quarter pole and eased out for racing room and made a four wide bid leaving the turn and finished willingly to be clearly second best. AFRICAN ANGEL pressed the pace three wide and made a two wide bid on the turn to gain the lead, then was headed by the winner at the quarter pole and weakened the final furlong, held show award. WARRIOR'S RANSOM was settled two wide early, came five wide into the lane and had no kick. DOCTOR ABBIE was settled back early, advanced on the inside on the turn and lacked a solid late rally. I CAME TO DANCE was settled early and tired. FILTERED LIGHT was settled early and four to five wide on the backstretch and tired. LADY LIGHTFEET set a pressured pace on the inside and stopped.
